>&gt; +		return -(s64)(vb-&gt;num_pages - v);<br />&gt; +	else<br />&gt; +		return v - vb-&gt;num_pages;<br /><br />What's wrong with just doing<br /><br />	return (s64)v - vb-&gt;num_pages;<br /><br />instead?<br /><br />Casting 'v' to s64 guarantees that the subtraction will eb done in 64 <br />bits, and the compiler can just generate the trivial non-conditional code.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
